title: Example accordion component
body:
An accordion is set of clickable sections, they are completely keyboard navigable.

You don't need an image for each of the sections, the ones used in this accordion are placeholders only, you can delete them out and use your own if you wish. 

There is no set amount of sections you have within an accordion but as a guide six a good maximum and three as a minimum


Please leave the instruction text in (or modify if needed) as this will give the instruction to screen readers.

title: Why make analysis reproducible?
body: Producing official statistics can be time-consuming and painstaking, because we need to make sure that our outputs are both accurate and timely.

title: Finding the right balance
body:
Finding balance is the key to implementing RAP successfully. This balance will vary across statistical products depending on the level of interaction and interpretation needed for the data.

Things to consider are:

title: Quality assuring data
body: We edit and validate data at different stages of the data journey. This may happen case-by-case (micro-editing), or for aggregated values (macro-editing). The quality of our statistics is impacted by the quality of the underlying data. Therefore, it is important that we understand the quality of our input data. Further information on understanding data quality can be found in the Data Quality e-learning course.
